<!-- ── FORMULA ── -->
<section class="content-section reveal">
  <h2>The Formula</h2>
  <p>Profit margin (as a percentage of revenue):</p>
  <div class="formula-box">
    Margin = (Revenue &minus; Cost) &divide; Revenue &times; 100
  </div>
  <p>Markup (as a percentage of cost):</p>
  <div class="formula-box">
    Markup = (Price &minus; Cost) &divide; Cost &times; 100
  </div>
  <p>Converting between them:</p>
  <div class="formula-box">
    Margin = Markup &divide; (1 + Markup &divide; 100) &times; 100
  </div>
  <p>Where:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Revenue / Price</strong> = what the customer pays</li>
    <li><strong>Cost</strong> = what you paid for the product or service</li>
    <li><strong>Margin</strong> = profit as a share of selling price</li>
    <li><strong>Markup</strong> = profit as a share of cost</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The critical difference: margin uses revenue as the denominator, markup uses cost. For the same product, <strong>markup is always higher than margin</strong>.</p>
</section>

